<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 04 at 1:32PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 215 PM CDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN GARVIN...SOUTHEASTERN CLEVELAND...NORTHWESTERN
PONTOTOC...SOUTHWESTERN POTTAWATOMIE AND SOUTHEASTERN MCCLAIN
COUNTIES...
At 131 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles southeast
of Wayne, moving east at 40 mph. A trained spotter observed half
dollar sized hail located on Highway 77 southeast of Wayne.
HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect damage
to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Locations impacted include...
Wayne, Paoli, Asher, Wanette, Byars, St. Louis and Rosedale.
HAIL THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.50 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
